The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Midnapore, Aug. 13: The CPM has expelled nearly 40 workers in the last one month in East Midnapore district for anti-party activities.

 Those who got the boot include Samiran Bera, the son of former CPM MLA from Moyna Dipak Bera. Samiran and four others in the Moyna zonal committee were charged with working against Mujibar Rahaman who won the Moyna seat this time by 10,000 votes. 

 CPM leader from East Midnapore Sudhir Giri said the party has a continuous process of cleaning the organisation of corrupt elements. 

 Calcutta: A teenager died after she fell off the roof of a three-storeyed building on Basak Street in Posta on Sunday afternoon. Officer-in-charge of Posta police station Swapan Kumar Ghosh said Khusboo Jain, 17, slipped while playing with her friends. Police have ruled out any foul play.

 Calcutta: A 32-year-old Forward Bloc worker was shot dead by a gang of four on Coal Dock Road in the South Port area on Sunday night. Police said Uma Mehta was locked in a land dispute with the four, who belonged to another political party. They assaulted him with a chopper before gunning him down, the police added.




